<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-250-087 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 391 214</DOCID><JOURNAL>CVGIP: Image Understanding  Jan 1991 v53 n1 p1(13).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Rigid body motion from range image sequences. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Horn, Berthold K.P.; Harris, John G.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A significant problem in autonomous navigation is recovery of thesix degrees of freedom of motion of a vehicle.andP;  A new algorithm ispresented that improves obstacle detection and avoidance.andP;  Theposition of the vehicle and the position of an obstacle can berelated even after the obstacle leaves the range camera's field ofview.andP;  This method also permits assembling of global maps of theterrain from registered information extracted from many rangeimages.andP;  The technique used is a least-squares minimization of thedifference between the measured rate of change of elevation at apoint and the rate predicted by the elevation rate constraintequation.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     AlgorithmsImage MotionResearch and DevelopmentMotor VehiclesObstacle AvoidanceObject Recognition.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotographchart.andO;Caption:   ERIM range scanner coordinate system. (chart)Constraint-point arrays. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>